19 payments on any individual does not exceed the total net benefit to
20 the state. Should neither the federal contractor nor the
21 subcontractor defer in part or in entirety their incentive payments
22 such that the total for all Quality Jobs quality jobs incentive
23 payments exceeds the total net benefit to the state, the priority
24 for incentive payments shall go to the entity with the earliest
Req. No. 17492 Page 50

1 reco gnized start date indentified identified within the current
2 Oklahoma Department of Commerce Quality Jobs quality jobs contract.
3 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 3606, as
4 last amended by Section 2, Chapter 29, 1st Extraordinary Session,
5 O.S.L. 2023 (68 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 3606), is amended to read
6 as follows:
7 Section 3606. A. As soon as practicable after the end of the
8 first complete calendar quarter following the start date, the
9 establishment shall file a claim for the payment with the Oklahoma
10 Tax Commission and shall specify the actual number and gross payroll
11 of new direct jobs for the establishment for the calendar quarter.
12 The Tax Commission shall verify the actual gross payroll for new
13 direct jobs for the establishment for such calendar quarter. If the
14 Tax Commission is not able to provide such verification utilizing
15 all available resources, the Tax Commission may request such
16 additional information from the establishment as may be necessary or
17 may request the establishment to revise its claim. An establishment
18 may file for an extension of the initial filing date with the
19 Oklahoma Department of Commerce. Any such extension shall be based
20 solely upon an extraordinary adverse business circumstance which
21 prevented the establishment from hiring the new direct jobs as
22 projected. If an establishment fails to file claims as required by
23 this section, it shall forfeit the right to receive any incentive
24 payments after three (3) years from the start date. If an
Req. No. 17492 Page 51

1 esta blishment has filed at least one claim pursuant to this section
2 but fails to file another claim within two (2) years of the most
3 recent claim, the Tax Commission, after consulting with the Oklahoma
4 Department of Commerce, may dismiss the establishment from the
5 program, forfeiting the establishment’s right to receive incentive
6 payments based on that contract.
7 B. 1. Except as otherwise provided in paragraph 2 of this
8 subsection, if the actual verified gross payroll for four (4)
9 consecutive calendar quarters does not equal or exceed the
10 applicable total required by Section 3604 of this title within three
11 (3) years of the start date, or does not equal or exceed the
12 applicable total required by Section 3604 of this title at any other
13 time during the ten-year period after the start date or during the
14 thirty-year period after the start date for establishments defined
15 or classified in the NAICS North American Industry Classification
16 System (NAICS) Manual under U.S. Industry No. 711211 (2007 version),
17 the incentive payments shall not be made and shall not be resumed
18 until such time as the actual verified gross payroll equals or
19 exceeds the amounts specified in Section 3604 of this title. If an
20 establishment fails to achieve the required gross payroll within
21 three (3) years of the start date, the establishment shall not make
22 a new or renewal application for incentive payments authorized
23 pursuant to the Oklahoma Quality Jobs Program Act for a period of
24 twelve (12) months from the last day of the last month of the three-
Req. No. 17492 Page 52

1 year period during which the required gross payroll amount was not
2 achieved.
3 2. Any establishment which does not meet the quarterly payroll
4 requirements provided pursuant to paragraph 1 of this subsection
5 during the time period which begins on April 1, 2020, and ends on
6 June 30, 2021, shall continue to receive incentive payments and
7 shall be exempt from the prescribed limitations.
8 C. If the average annualized wage required for an establishment
9 does not equal or exceed the amount specified in paragraph 1 or 2 of
10 subsection F of Section 3604 of this title during any calendar
11 quarter, the incentive payments shall not be made and shall not be
12 resumed until such time as such requirements are met.
13 D. In no event shall incentive payments, cumulatively, exceed
14 the estimated net direct state benefits, except for establishments
15 subject to the provisions of subparagraph d of paragraph 7 of
16 subsection A of Section 3603 of this title.
17 E. An establishment that has qualified pursuant to Section 3604
18 of this title may receive payments only in accordance with the
19 provisions of the law under which it initially applied and was
20 approved. If an establishment that is receiving incentive payments
21 expands, it may apply for additional incentive payments based on the
22 gross payroll anticipated from the expansion only, pursuant to
23 Section 3604 of this title. Provided, an establishment which has
24 suffered an extraordinary adverse business circumstance, as
Req. No. 17492 Page 53

1 cert ified by the Incentive Approval Committee, may be allowed to
2 voluntarily withdraw from the Oklahoma Quality Jobs Program, repay
3 to the Tax Commission the total amount of incentive payments
4 received pursuant to the provisions of this section, plus interest
5 at the rate specified in Section 727.1 of Title 12 of the Oklahoma
6 Statutes, and reapply to the Department for a new incentive contract
7 if the establishment qualifies pursuant to the provisions of the
8 Oklahoma Quality Jobs Program Act. Any funds received by the Tax
9 Commission pursuant to the provisions of this subsection shall be
10 apportioned in the manner that income tax revenues are apportioned.
11 F. An establishment that is receiving incentive payments may
12 not apply for additional incentive payments for any new projects
13 until twelve (12) quarters after receipt of the first incentive
14 payment, or until the establishment’s actual verified gross payroll
15 for new direct jobs equals or exceeds Two Million Five Hundred
16 Thousand Dollars ($2,500,000.00) during any four consecutive-
17 calendar-quarter period, whichever comes first. After meeting the
18 requirements of this subsection, an establishment may apply for
19 additional incentive payments based upon the gross payroll
20 anticipated from an expansion only.
21 G. As soon as practicable after verification of the actual
22 gross payroll as required by this section and except as otherwise
23 provided by subsection K of Section 3604 of this title, the Tax
24 Commission shall issue a warrant to the establishment in the amount
Req. No. 17492 Page 54

1 of t he net benefit rate multiplied by the actual gross payroll as
2 determined pursuant to subsection A of this section for the calendar
3 quarter.
4 H. If after three (3) years of the start date, an establishment
5 fails to submit filings to the Oklahoma Tax Commission on an annual
6 basis, the establishment may be dismissed from the Oklahoma Quality
7 Jobs Program by the Oklahoma Department of Commerce. If an
8 establishment is dismissed from the Oklahoma Quality Jobs Program by
9 the Oklahoma Department of Commerce, no additional incentive
10 payments shall be made to the establishment after dismissal.
11 SECTION 5. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 3905, is
12 amended to read as follows:
13 Section 3905. A. 1. Beginning with the first complete
14 calendar quarter after the application of the establishment is
15 approved by the Oklahoma Department of Commerce, the establishment
16 shall begin filing quarterly reports with the Oklahoma Tax
17 Commission that specify the actual number and individual gross
18 taxable payroll of new direct jobs for the establishment and such
19 other information as required by the Tax Commission. In no event
20 shall the first claim for incentive payments be filed later than
21 three (3) years from the start date designated by the Department.
22 The Tax Commission shall verify the actual individual gross taxable
23 payroll for new direct jobs. If the Tax Commission is not able to
24 provide such verification utilizing all available resources, the Tax
Req. No. 17492 Page 55

1 Comm ission may request additional information from the establishment
2 as may be necessary or may request the establishment to revise its
3 reports.
4 The establishment shall continue filing such reports during the
5 seven-year incentive period or until it is no longer qualified to
6 receive incentive payments. Such reports shall constitute a claim
7 for quarterly incentive payments by the establishment.
8 2. Upon receipt of a report for the initial calendar quarter of
9 the incentive period and for each subsequent calendar quarter
10 thereafter, the Tax Commission shall determine if the establishment
11 has met the following requirements:
12 a. created and or maintained the minimum number of new
13 direct jobs as specified in paragraph 3 of subsection
14 C of Section 3904 of this title, and
15 b. paid the individuals it employed in new direct jobs an
16 annualized wage which equaled or exceeded the
17 applicable percentage of the average county wage as
18 that percentage was determined by the Oklahoma
19 Department of Commerce upon approval of the
20 application.
21 3. Upon determining that an establishment has met the
22 requirements of paragraph 2 of this subsection for the initial
23 calendar quarter of the incentive period, the Tax Commission shall
24 issue a warrant to the establishment in an amount which shall be
Req. No. 17492 Page 56

1 equa l to the net benefit rate multiplied by the amount of gross
2 taxable payroll of new direct jobs actually paid by the
3 establishment.
4 B. Except as provided in subsection C of this section, the
5 quarterly incentive payment provided for in subsection A of this
6 section shall be allowed in each of the twenty-seven subsequent
7 calendar quarters.
8 C. 1. An establishment which does not meet the requirements of
9 paragraph 2 of subsection A of this section within twelve (12)
10 months of the date of its application, or after July 1, 2011, within
11 twenty-four (24) months of the date of its application, shall be
12 ineligible to receive any incentive payments pursuant to its
13 application and approval.
14 2. An establishment which at any time during the twenty-seven
