18 such requirements are not met.
19 SECTION 6. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 3914, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 3914. A. Except for the payment amount required by
22 subsection E of this section, an establishment which meets the
23 qualifications specified in the 21st Century Quality Jobs Incentive
24 Act may receive quarterly incentive payments for a ten-year period
Req. No. 17492 Page 57

1 from the Oklahoma Tax Commission pursuant to the provisions of this
2 act the 21st Century Quality Jobs Incentive Act, as verified by the
3 Tax Commission, in an amount equal to:
4 1. The gross payroll multiplied by the initial net benefit rate
5 until such time as the establishment creates ten new direct jobs; or
6 2. The gross payroll multiplied by the fulfillment net benefit
7 rate after such time as the establishment created and maintains ten
8 new direct jobs.
9 B. In order to receive incentive payments, an establishment
10 shall apply to the Oklahoma Department of Commerce. The application
11 shall be on a form prescribed by the Department and shall contain
12 such information as may be required by the Department to determine
13 if the applicant is qualified. The establishment may apply for an
14 effective date for a project, which shall not be more than twelve
15 (12) months from the date the application is submitted to the
16 Department.
17 C. Before approving an application for incentive payments, the
18 Department must first determine that the applicant meets the
19 following requirements:
20 1. Be engaged in a basic industry as defined in the 21st
21 Century Quality Jobs Incentive Act;
22 2. Will hire at least ten full-time employees in this state
23 within twelve (12) quarters of the date of application;
24
Req. No. 17492 Page 58

1 3. Will pay the individuals it employs in new direct jobs an
2 average annualized wage which equals or exceeds three hundred
3 percent (300%) of the average county wage for the county in which
4 the applicant is located as that percentage is determined by the
5 Oklahoma Department of Commerce based on the most recent U.S. United
6 States Department of Commerce data. For purposes of this paragraph,
7 health care premiums paid by the applicant for individuals in new
8 direct jobs shall not be included in the annualized wage. Provided,
9 no average wage requirement shall exceed Ninety-four Thousand
10 Dollars ($94,000.00) in any county. This maximum wage threshold
11 shall be indexed and modified from time to time based on the latest
12 Consumer Price Index year-to-date percent change release as of the
13 date of the annual average county wage data release from the Bureau
14 of Economic Analysis of the U.S. United States Department of
15 Commerce;
16 4. Has a basic health benefit plan which, as determined by the
17 Department, meets the elements established under divisions (1)
18 through (7) of subparagraph b of paragraph 1 of subsection A of
19 Section 3603 of this title and which will be offered to individuals
20 within twelve (12) months of employment in a new direct job;
21 5. Has not received incentive payments under the Small Employer
22 Quality Jobs Program Incentive Act, the Saving Quality Jobs Act or
23 the Former Military Facility Development Act; and
24
Req. No. 17492 Page 59

1 6. Is not qualified for approval of an application for
2 incentive payments under the Small Employer Quality Jobs Program
3 Incentive Act, the Saving Quality Jobs Act or the Former Military
4 Facility Development Act.
